<br>
I never really picked up on soloing tactics as I was always in a group, so I'm lost. <br>
<br>
Using the lists I've found on here of places to solo, I've come to the conclusion that my tactics for soloing are less than ideal as I find myself running, gating, and zoning from countless mobs that other people &quot;have soloed but was a little tough&quot;.<br>
<br>
I guess really I need more than just places to solo. <br>
<br>
For example, the first room in Kedge was suggested. I had no trouble with the mobs there except for that damn Lancer, but according to a couple of posts he WAS soloable. (Even though an even con to me)<br>
<br>
Basically, I try to malise to pull a mob, send pet in, wait a few seconds and throw a nuke, wait a few more seconds and throw a nuke. I've got my heal spell up all the time, but I find usually if I use it, I never can keep the pet's health ahead of the mob, and feel like I would have been better off nuking. <br>
<br>
So there's my story. I'm just a little bit confused, and really frustrated at this point. I REALLY love this class, and refuse to play anything else. So I guess it's time I suck it up and learn what the hell I'm doing. =)  <br>
<br>
Beltaine Winterfyre -- 39th Magician<br>
Lost Order of Akalabeth<br>
Veeshan Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#333333>(4/4/02 9:25:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=361.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pet and faction</span><hr size=1> I bet you are referring to the piercer/impaler swordfish in Kedge...<br>
